INSERT INTO `comments` VALUES (1,'album',67,1,'It was tough to pick a best Brian Jonestown Massacre album, but this one is pretty damn good.','2017-05-08 00:00:00',0),(2,'album',94,1,'This is about as far out and angular as it gets!  A challenging listen, but once you get used to it, it is worth it.','2017-05-08 00:00:00',0),(3,'album',90,1,'It was between this one and Los Angeles.  Close.','2017-05-08 00:00:00',0),(4,'album',4,1,'This album is my favorite recent discovery. Psychotic blues mixed with a touch of something exotic. Very trippy stuff.','2017-05-08 00:00:00',0),(5,'album',91,1,'Interesting droney sleepytime pieces.  I would use this for background music. Good background music.','2017-05-10 00:00:00',0),(6,'album',7,1,'I\'m not really sure which Ariel Pink album I like best, and if I like the lo-fi stuff better than the new stuff.  They are both really good, so I guess for me it is a tie.','2017-05-16 00:00:00',0),(7,'album',70,1,'I like the short songs, and the bass is pretty intense.  Never really got into the Minutemen somehow, but after giving this album a listen I can see why so many people did.','2017-05-19 00:00:00',0),(8,'album',97,3,'This is actually one of my least liked Doors albums.  It\'s still \"good\", but never comes up as something I feel like listening to.','2017-05-25 00:00:00',0),(9,'album',97,1,'Wow, my least favorite Doors album is probably Soft Parade.  Other than that they are all 4\'s or 5\'s for me.  Mostly 5\'s.  I\'m not including the post Jim Morrison album obviously.','2017-05-25 00:00:00',0),(10,'album',59,1,'This is a really great album, I will probably change my rating to a 5 once I hear it a few times.','2017-05-25 00:00:00',0),(11,'album',64,1,'Interesting listen.  Not at all what I expected.  I will have to give it another listen before I can really tell how much I like it, but it\'s at least a 3 for originality.','2017-05-25 00:00:00',0),(12,'album',58,1,'His fingerpicking is just insane.  I love acoustic blues... well electric too, but the old acoustic stuff just has such a haunting sound.','2017-05-26 00:00:00',0),(13,'album',64,3,'What\'s funny is that Keiran and I both liked this album despite its obscurity.  Not sure how we both ended up finding it.  The guy from Talk Talk wrote 1 pop album to finance his \"real\" music career.  He just wanted to make good music, but also wanted the funding to do it.  So he wrote some 80\'s new wave, made a ton of money from one album, then did what he wanted.','2017-06-04 00:00:00',0),(14,'album',60,1,'I liked some of the songs, and it seems to have good potential but maybe I just didn\'t get some of it, sometimes I felt like I was at some old dead head\'s house with his buddies.  (Not that in itself that is a bad thing, but sometimes it felt a little flat to me).','2017-06-06 00:00:00',0),(15,'album',97,3,'This comes in 4th out of the 6 with Morrison. Soft Parade and LA Woman aren\'t even on my radar though, so this is my least favorite of their \"good\" stuff.  I think that\'s a better way to put it.','2017-06-11 00:00:00',0),(16,'album',24,1,'\"You know what the kids are listening to today?  Disco Motherfucker!\" - Oates','2017-07-10 00:00:00',0),(17,'album',80,5,'Probably will be a 5 after further listening. Great so far!','2018-02-23 00:00:00',0),(32,'album',133,1,'Famous for showcasing Beatles recording techniques and psychedelic style.','2025-09-21 15:39:50',1);
